you're getting the support you need.

25:53.468 --> 25:55.929
I... kinda just wanna put
all this stuff away.

25:58.306 --> 25:59.626
So you don't wanna talk about it?

25:59.683 --> 26:01.893
No, I'll talk about anything.
I just wanna...

26:02.352 --> 26:04.020
I just kinda wanna get this done.

26:13.196 --> 26:14.239
All right.

26:23.790 --> 26:25.667
You call me if you need anything, okay?

26:25.750 --> 26:26.876
Okay, will do.

26:45.770 --> 26:47.647
Hey, Judith, it's me.

26:47.939 --> 26:50.108
Yeah, I'm just leaving her place now.

26:51.651 --> 26:55.071
Honestly, I have no idea how she is.

26:55.488 --> 26:56.615
She seemed...

26:57.407 --> 26:58.867
I don't know, fine.

26:59.534 --> 27:01.870
Like... like nothing had happened.

27:02.245 --> 27:05.290
It was weird that I was even
visiting her or something.

27:06.666 --> 27:10.670
- Oh, Barlow. I need a copy of a DCFS file.
- Yeah.

27:11.421 --> 27:13.702
It's for the victim of that sexual assault
at the Oakdale.

27:14.090 --> 27:15.675
- Got it. I'm on it.
- Thank you.

27:35.445 --> 27:36.445
Parker.

27:38.531 --> 27:39.741
Right, sure.

27:40.825 --> 27:42.619
How, uh... How you doing today?

27:44.704 --> 27:46.915
Would it be okay
if this stayed between us?

27:47.999 --> 27:51.211
- You don't want me to take notes?
- I'd rather it be in confidence.

27:51.294 --> 27:53.254
I don't want it getting back to Marie.

27:54.547 --> 27:56.675
Sure, I can do that.

27:58.259 --> 27:59.678
I love her, I do.

28:00.387 --> 28:03.098
She was with me the last two years.

28:03.181 --> 28:05.725
- She came here from Colleen's.
- Who's Colleen?

28:05.809 --> 28:06.935
Another foster mom.

28:07.185 --> 28:11.064
Marie was with Colleen for a couple
of weeks before she came to me.

28:11.815 --> 28:14.734
Isn't that kind of, um, a short stint?

28:14.818 --> 28:18.113
It was an emergency thing.
The home Marie was in before was...

28:18.988 --> 28:21.741
Well... they had to get her out of there.

28:21.991 --> 28:23.159
So, she went to Colleen's,

28:23.243 --> 28:26.121
but Colleen had a full house,
so she couldn't keep her long-term.

28:26.204 --> 28:27.747
- So, she came to you.
- Right.

28:27.831 --> 28:30.041
And she was my first foster child.

28:30.125 --> 28:32.293
I thought
they were gonna give me an infant.

28:32.377 --> 28:34.379
I had a crib and everything.

28:34.462 --> 28:36.631
And then this 16-year-old shows up.

28:36.715 --> 28:37.966
Must have been a surprise.

28:38.049 --> 28:40.593
Oh, I was fine with it. I love teenagers.

28:41.136 --> 28:44.514
I work at a high school
in the principal's office, so...

28:45.265 --> 28:47.726
I see a lot of them all day long.

28:47.809 --> 28:48.809
Got it.

28:49.144 --> 28:50.395
So, you know,

28:51.104 --> 28:54.399
her behaviors, what she was going through,
it was all pretty familiar.

28:54.482 --> 28:56.943
Well, it must have made it, uh, easier.

28:57.026 --> 28:58.862
For me, I don't know if it did for her.

28:58.945 --> 29:00.447
I... I hope it did.

29:02.115 --> 29:06.244
My point is, she's had a hard life.

29:06.327 --> 29:08.872
And not just the home she came from.

29:08.955 --> 29:09.955
But...

29:10.582 --> 29:11.958
some of the foster homes too.

29:12.041 --> 29:15.336
Has she been in situations
you'd call, um...

29:16.254 --> 29:17.422
abusive?

29:17.505 --> 29:19.215
Some, yeah.

29:20.675 --> 29:25.221
And that makes for
a very complicated young woman.

29:25.680 --> 29:28.600
Then you add this move,
being on her own for the first time.

29:28.850 --> 29:30.310
How long ago did she move out?

29:30.393 --> 29:31.770
About six months ago.

29:31.853 --> 29:34.022
And the transition's been hard?

29:34.105 --> 29:37.442
It's change. And change is stressful.
So, yeah.

29:38.193 --> 29:39.986
She has been a little needier.

29:40.069 --> 29:42.363
A little more acting out.

29:43.364 --> 29:44.741
Acting out how?

29:48.036 --> 29:51.664
It's got one of those deals
with the hotel and rent.

29:54.250 --> 29:56.169
That's inappropriate. Marie!

29:56.920 --> 29:58.171
Marie!

30:00.298 --> 30:01.841
Honey, settle down.

30:03.760 --> 30:05.011
Marie, that's enough.

30:05.428 --> 30:06.429
Marie.

30:06.513 --> 30:09.265
Hey, hey. Get off the table! Marie!

30:09.349 --> 30:11.768
Marie, there are children present. Enough!

30:13.770 --> 30:15.480
- Off the table. Right now!
- What?

30:15.563 --> 30:16.791
- Right now!
- Why do I have to...

30:16.815 --> 30:20.610
Just a whole lot of what I call
look-at-me behavior.

30:21.152 --> 30:24.656
<i>♪...birthday to you ♪</i>

30:28.535 --> 30:30.119
It's okay, honey.

30:30.662 --> 30:33.081
And overly sensitive overly contrary.

30:33.873 --> 30:36.543
All normal, given the circumstances.

30:36.626 --> 30:39.045
Yeah, sure, it's sounds like, uh,
a big change.

30:39.128 --> 30:41.089
I didn't think she was ready for it.

30:41.172 --> 30:45.301
- But she insisted, so I supported her.
- Right.

30:45.635 --> 30:48.930
So, anyway, yesterday morning
she called and told me what happened.

30:49.013 --> 30:50.431
- The rape.
- Yes.

30:50.932 --> 30:53.309
And I was just horrified.

30:53.810 --> 30:55.311
Angry, upset, worried...

30:55.395 --> 30:56.229
all of it.

30:56.312 --> 30:58.648
I went straight over there,
right away, and...

31:03.444 --> 31:06.114
I don't know. The whole thing just felt...

31:07.991 --> 31:08.991
off.

31:10.785 --> 31:12.370
Off, how?

31:12.453 --> 31:13.872
Just not right.

31:13.955 --> 31:17.333
How she was acting and re-acting.
Well, you saw her.

31:17.792 --> 31:20.670
She was detached, I guess.

31:20.753 --> 31:24.632
I think there's a range of reactions
to this kind of thing.

31:24.716 --> 31:26.843
- I know, believe me.
- Hmm.

31:26.926 --> 31:30.388
I have my own experience with it.

31:30.847 --> 31:32.223
Your own experience?

31:32.640 --> 31:36.185
I was sexually assaulted in my 20s.

31:36.269 --> 31:39.188
A guy I was dating.

31:39.272 --> 31:40.690
- I'm sorry.
- Thank you.

31:41.399 --> 31:43.568
My point is, I know about this.

31:43.651 --> 31:45.731
And given the way she was acting
and everything else,

31:45.778 --> 31:48.406
I don't know, it just all felt...

31:49.657 --> 31:51.993
- Off.
- And then those weird details.

31:52.076 --> 31:54.579
He brought a blindfold
but nothing to tie her with.

31:54.662 --> 31:56.456
Would a shoelace even hold her?

31:56.956 --> 31:59.584
And then that thing about him
taking the picture.

32:00.919 --> 32:02.503
- What... what about it?
- Well...

32:02.795 --> 32:04.005
just hypothetically.

32:04.797 --> 32:07.592
Say she's gotten herself into a situation
with some boy.

32:07.967 --> 32:12.263
And there is a compromising picture
out there, or she thinks there might be.

32:13.264 --> 32:14.682
Are you saying

32:15.308 --> 32:17.060
you think Marie

32:17.894 --> 32:18.978
made up the attack?

32:19.062 --> 32:22.398
I am not drawing any conclusions.
I just...

32:25.276 --> 32:27.570
I woke up this morning with all this stuff

32:28.154 --> 32:29.656
spinning around in my head,

32:29.739 --> 32:34.285
and I thought you guys
should have the whole picture.

32:34.661 --> 32:36.037
The context.

32:37.413 --> 32:38.623
I might not have even called,

32:38.706 --> 32:42.085
but then I talked to Colleen, and she said
she was feeling weird about it too.

32:42.168 --> 32:44.462
So, you both have some doubts
about Marie's story?

32:44.545 --> 32:45.713
Not doubts.

32:45.797 --> 32:49.300
I just thought since I had this...
feeling...

32:52.220 --> 32:56.641
maybe I had an obligation
to share it with you.

33:19.122 --> 33:20.123
Can I go now?

33:28.214 --> 33:29.924
Sure. Here, I'll walk you out.

33:32.677 --> 33:35.346
Let me ask you one thing,
so I'm sure I understand.

33:35.888 --> 33:41.060
Uh, in your statement you wrote
that you tried calling Connor,

33:42.145 --> 33:43.479
then called Judith,

33:44.647 --> 33:46.107
then cut yourself free.

33:46.482 --> 33:47.483
Yeah.

33:49.027 --> 33:50.111
In that order.

33:50.194 --> 33:51.194
Yeah.

33:53.614 --> 33:55.199
All right, thanks again, Marie.

33:55.950 --> 33:57.035
You're welcome.

34:04.584 --> 34:07.003
<i>She told us
you were the first person she called</i>

34:07.086 --> 34:08.212
<i>after the attack.</i>

34:08.670 --> 34:10.882
Yeah, she told me that too. I felt so bad.

34:11.799 --> 34:14.594
I didn't hear it.
I don't sleep with my phone in my room.

34:14.677 --> 34:16.721
- So, you two are close?
- Yeah.

34:17.929 --> 34:19.389
Friends, more than friends?

34:19.974 --> 34:20.808
Friends.

34:20.891 --> 34:23.936
We... We used to date, but...

34:24.020 --> 34:27.523
Are you and she sexually active?

34:28.107 --> 34:29.108
Um...

34:29.692 --> 34:31.694
Not... No, not, not... No.

34:33.029 --> 34:34.280
When she called,

34:34.822 --> 34:37.199
the morning of the assault,
did she leave a message?

34:39.409 --> 34:40.536
Mm-mm.

34:41.411 --> 34:44.123
- She just hung up.
- Can I confirm that on your call log?

34:45.333 --> 34:47.001
Oh, uh, sure.

34:53.091 --> 34:54.091
Here it is.

34:54.132 --> 34:55.132
Thanks.

34:55.842 --> 34:59.055
And then, uh, when was it
you finally talked to her?

34:59.138 --> 35:00.681
She called that night.

35:01.599 --> 35:02.600
Um...

35:04.852 --> 35:06.020
10:48.

35:07.563 --> 35:08.606
And what did she tell you?

35:10.858 --> 35:13.069
That, um, she had been raped.

35:13.152 --> 35:14.821
And did she give you any specifics?

35:14.904 --> 35:18.116
Yeah. She said that she woke up,

35:18.199 --> 35:21.202
and a man was there with a knife.

35:21.285 --> 35:23.079
Did she describe him physically?

35:24.539 --> 35:25.539
Uh-uh.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.542
But I guess after the, um...

35:28.626 --> 35:29.626
the rape...

35:30.002 --> 35:32.296
um, she said he left.

35:33.256 --> 35:35.049
Did she say what happened next?

35:35.133 --> 35:37.593
Yeah. I guess she was still, uh...

35:38.302 --> 35:39.637
um, tied up.

35:39.971 --> 35:42.431
So, she dialed the phone with her toes.

35:43.724 --> 35:44.767
With her toes?

35:47.937 --> 35:49.063
You sure about that?

35:50.565 --> 35:52.483
I mean, yeah, that's what she said.

35:53.734 --> 35:55.236
Dialing with your toes.

35:55.945 --> 35:58.990
Not really a detail
you'd be inclined to forget, you know?

35:59.073 --> 36:01.033
The hard evidence we have:

36:01.117 --> 36:03.786
the shoelaces are from her shoes,
the knife's from her kitchen.

36:03.870 --> 36:05.371
No sign of forced entry.

36:05.746 --> 36:07.331
No identifiable prints.

36:07.415 --> 36:08.416
No body fluids.

36:08.499 --> 36:11.335
Hey, Detective, here's that
Child and Family Services file.

36:11.419 --> 36:12.920
Uh, great. Thank you.

36:13.004 --> 36:14.004
Is that hers?

36:14.297 --> 36:15.298
Yeah.

36:17.758 --> 36:18.801
Aw, man.

36:29.395 --> 36:30.395
Jesus.

36:35.943 --> 36:37.069
Marie?

36:40.323 --> 36:41.323
Marie!

36:42.116 --> 36:43.326
What are you doing?

36:43.868 --> 36:45.870
<i>Customer needs assistance.</i>

36:45.953 --> 36:48.956
- Um...
- That's cookware. These are vacuums.

36:51.709 --> 36:55.129
I'm sorry. Uh, shoot.
Wh... where do these go again?

36:55.213 --> 36:57.256
Forget it. Rami.

37:10.102 --> 37:11.102
Hello?

37:11.354 --> 37:13.064
<i>Marie, it's Detective Parker.</i>

37:15.566 --> 37:16.734
Oh, hi.

37:17.235 --> 37:19.570
<i>Listen, I was wondering
if we could meet again.</i>

37:22.531 --> 37:23.531
Why?

37:25.284 --> 37:26.369
Am I in trouble?

37:33.834 --> 37:34.835
What?

37:34.919 --> 37:36.963
She asked if she was in trouble.

37:37.755 --> 37:38.589
Hmm.

37:38.673 --> 37:42.260
In my experience, when someone asks,
"Am I in trouble?"

37:42.343 --> 37:43.343
Yeah.

37:43.761 --> 37:45.137
They usually are.

37:47.265 --> 37:49.183
Okay, I'm gonna cut to the chase.

37:49.267 --> 37:52.561
I found some inconsistencies
in your statements

37:52.645 --> 37:54.522
and those of other witnesses.

37:57.483 --> 38:00.278
I... I don't know anything about that.

38:00.361 --> 38:03.656
How about you walk me through it again.
Tell me exactly how the assault happened.

38:04.115 --> 38:06.075
- Again?
- One more time, yes.

38:09.829 --> 38:11.414
Okay, I...

38:12.415 --> 38:14.166
was in bed, asleep.

38:21.173 --> 38:26.137
Marie, I'd like to back up a little
and talk about what came before all this.

38:27.471 --> 38:29.974
DCFS shared your file with us.

38:32.143 --> 38:35.354
- Why?
- We wanted a clear picture of who you are

38:36.063 --> 38:38.983
beyond this assault, as a person.

38:41.402 --> 38:42.402
Oh.

38:42.987 --> 38:44.739
You've been through a lot.

38:45.156 --> 38:46.907
You're a real survivor, aren't ya?

38:47.408 --> 38:48.993
I mean, no dad, uh...

38:49.660 --> 38:52.621
unreliable mom
with not-so-nice boyfriends.

38:52.705 --> 38:56.292
Then foster care,
which wasn't always much better, I'm sure.

38:56.375 --> 38:58.711
Sometimes... sometimes it was good.

38:58.794 --> 39:02.465
My point is... you've made it through
some very difficult stuff.

39:02.548 --> 39:05.676
I don't really like to think about that.
I just try to be as...

39:07.762 --> 39:08.929
happy as I can be.

39:09.013 --> 39:11.766
- And as happy as possible, so...
- Sure, I get that.

39:11.849 --> 39:12.849
So, help us out.

39:13.434 --> 39:17.063
There are inconsistencies in your story.

39:18.272 --> 39:20.941
I mean, the dialing alone,
we have four different versions:

39:21.025 --> 39:24.028
tied, untied, with your hands,
with your toes...

39:24.111 --> 39:25.154
I dialed with my hands.

39:25.237 --> 39:27.037
Then why'd you tell Connor
you used your toes?

39:27.073 --> 39:28.074
I don't...

39:29.992 --> 39:31.035
Maybe I did.

39:31.118 --> 39:32.918
- You just told us you didn't.
- Well, it's...

39:34.121 --> 39:35.121
What?

39:35.373 --> 39:36.415
I don't...

39:37.833 --> 39:39.210
It's... it's confusing.

39:39.293 --> 39:40.293
For us too.

39:40.544 --> 39:42.213
And we're not the only ones.

39:45.633 --> 39:46.550
W... what do you mean?

39:46.634 --> 39:51.013
There are other people who don't know
that what you told us about the rape...

39:52.098 --> 39:53.599
that it's the truth.

39:55.434 --> 39:57.645
- Who?
- Well, Judith for one.

39:57.728 --> 39:58.771
She said that?

39:58.854 --> 40:00.564
And Connor's statement.

40:01.399 --> 40:02.441
What... what about it?

40:02.525 --> 40:04.610
It's also inconsistent with yours.

40:04.693 --> 40:07.363
So, he knows the version you told him.

40:08.197 --> 40:10.077
And then he finds out
it's not what you told us.

40:10.116 --> 40:12.910
It makes it very hard for him
to believe you too.

40:12.993 --> 40:14.745
He said that he didn't believe me?

40:15.371 --> 40:17.540
I don't... Wh... why would he...
why would he say that?

40:17.623 --> 40:19.017
And then there's the crime scene.

40:19.041 --> 40:21.210
I mean, we couldn't find
any physical evidence

40:21.293 --> 40:23.963
there was anyone else
in your apartment that night.

40:24.046 --> 40:25.714
But there was.

40:25.798 --> 40:30.094
Marie, I want to be really clear
about something.

40:30.469 --> 40:32.721
We don't think you're a bad person.

40:32.805 --> 40:33.931
Absolutely not.

40:34.014 --> 40:37.560
And I also don't think this was some
big, thought-out thing,

40:37.643 --> 40:41.856
but given the inconsistencies
in your story and the lack of evidence,

40:41.939 --> 40:45.192
this is becoming a puzzle
that is hard for us to piece together.

40:45.276 --> 40:46.277
Right, so...

40:47.236 --> 40:50.739
I'm gonna tell you a version
that does fit together.

40:51.157 --> 40:52.157
Okay?

40:52.783 --> 40:55.327
A young woman,
been through a ton of bad stuff,

40:55.411 --> 40:57.288
on her own for the first time,

40:57.371 --> 40:59.248
just broke up with her boyfriend,

40:59.874 --> 41:02.251
feeling isolated, lonely,

41:02.751 --> 41:03.751
might...

41:04.545 --> 41:06.005
on the spur of the moment,

41:06.755 --> 41:10.384
come up with something,
without thinking it through,

41:11.844 --> 41:14.472
that would get her the attention
she needs.

41:14.555 --> 41:18.017
'Cause you haven't gotten enough attention
in your life. I can see that.

41:19.810 --> 41:22.897
You haven't been cared for
or protected, and...

41:24.732 --> 41:26.192
that's not your fault.

41:27.401 --> 41:29.153
So, Marie...

41:30.446 --> 41:31.446
tell us.

41:31.739 --> 41:33.908
We need to know. It's our job.

41:34.950 --> 41:38.996
Is there really a rapist running around
that we should be looking for?

41:41.999 --> 41:43.042
Marie?

41:46.003 --> 41:48.803
Marie, we can't
leave here till you give us an answer.

41:54.470 --> 41:55.470
Say it.

42:05.773 --> 42:06.773
No.

42:07.441 --> 42:08.943
There was no rapist?

42:10.236 --> 42:11.946
No one came in your apartment?

42:12.738 --> 42:13.864
And the...

42:14.949 --> 42:17.243
shoelaces, the knife... you did that?

42:21.372 --> 42:22.372
Okay.

42:24.124 --> 42:25.376
Thank you, Marie.

42:26.126 --> 42:27.253
Can I go now?

42:27.962 --> 42:29.463
We need a statement.

42:30.589 --> 42:31.589
Right.

42:32.049 --> 42:33.049
Uh...

42:34.635 --> 42:37.054
Since your other statement's already
in the file,

42:37.137 --> 42:39.014
we need you to write a new one...

42:40.057 --> 42:41.892
with this new information.

42:42.935 --> 42:43.936
Okay?

42:48.357 --> 42:49.775
Here. Same deal.

42:49.858 --> 42:52.069
Fill it out with what you just told us,

42:52.152 --> 42:54.863
and then, yeah, you can go home.

43:11.589 --> 43:12.881
Well, that's that.

43:13.966 --> 43:15.801
- Jesus.
- Yeah.

43:20.389 --> 43:22.349
I tell ya, I'm glad we caught it early.

43:22.975 --> 43:25.603
Remember that case over
in King County last year?

43:25.686 --> 43:27.813
College student and the history professor?

43:28.355 --> 43:31.150
Guy spent a week in jail
before she admitted she made it up.

43:32.192 --> 43:33.360
Didn't he sue her?

43:33.944 --> 43:35.321
I think he did, yeah.

43:36.155 --> 43:37.239
I don't blame him.

43:39.033 --> 43:40.284
I feel for her though.

43:41.285 --> 43:44.121
I mean, Christ, feeding a little girl
dog food. Who does that?

43:44.747 --> 43:47.291
You can't take care of a kid,
use a fucking condom.

43:47.374 --> 43:49.376
- God.
- Simple.

43:52.713 --> 43:53.881
Change?

43:53.964 --> 43:55.591
Oh, God.

44:04.933 --> 44:05.934
There you go.

44:07.645 --> 44:08.896
You have a ride home?

44:09.938 --> 44:11.315
I can take the bus.

44:11.982 --> 44:13.734
You sure? We can give you a lift.

44:13.817 --> 44:14.817
No, that's okay.

44:15.027 --> 44:16.945
- I can have these?
- Yeah, all yours.

44:19.615 --> 44:20.449
Hang on.

44:21.575 --> 44:22.951
What is this?

44:23.035 --> 44:24.870
This is not what you just said.

44:26.246 --> 44:28.582
"I dreamed that I was raped.

44:28.666 --> 44:32.628
When I woke up, it felt so real,
I believed that it had happened."

44:33.545 --> 44:34.545
Marie,

44:34.880 --> 44:36.048
what's going on?

44:36.548 --> 44:38.926
You just said there was no rape.

44:39.968 --> 44:41.261
You just said that.

44:43.347 --> 44:44.181
Sit down.

44:44.264 --> 44:45.557
Come on, sit back down.

44:50.521 --> 44:52.022
Let me explain something.

44:52.481 --> 44:55.401
Our job, mine and Detective Parker's,

44:56.860 --> 44:58.821
is to protect the public.

44:59.363 --> 45:01.448
That's it, that's the whole gig.

45:01.532 --> 45:03.367
Time in here with a witness,

45:04.034 --> 45:06.370
that's time that we could be
out on the street,

45:06.870 --> 45:08.247
keeping people safe.

45:08.580 --> 45:12.042
Now, that's part of the job, it's fine.
We're happy to do it,

45:12.126 --> 45:14.920
as long as the time in here is valuable.

45:15.003 --> 45:17.089
If it's about something real.

45:17.172 --> 45:19.925
This is not a worthwhile use of our time.

45:20.300 --> 45:22.010
This is a waste of our time.

45:33.772 --> 45:35.649
I'm pretty positive that it happened.

45:35.733 --> 45:38.193
Pretty positive or positive?

45:39.236 --> 45:40.821
M... maybe I blocked it out.

45:43.073 --> 45:44.450
- Marie.
- Hmm.

45:44.533 --> 45:47.077
You're a smart
young woman, clearly.

45:47.161 --> 45:50.122
You must understand
the way you're handling this...

45:51.749 --> 45:54.501
You say one thing, you write another.

45:55.169 --> 45:57.713
There is a rapist, there isn't one.

45:58.464 --> 46:00.799
It's a dream, it's a blackout.

46:00.883 --> 46:03.927
You've told us four different versions.

46:04.011 --> 46:06.597
At this point,
regardless of what the truth is,

46:06.680 --> 46:11.727
the only thing we know for sure is
that you have told us at least three lies.

46:16.565 --> 46:18.275
What do you think should happen...

46:19.193 --> 46:20.527
to someone who would...

46:21.862 --> 46:23.906
lie about something like this?

46:28.911 --> 46:30.579
I should get counseling?

47:05.531 --> 47:06.532
Okay.

47:11.119 --> 47:12.246
Okay, what?

47:14.122 --> 47:15.958
Okay, I'll write the statement now.

47:38.272 --> 47:39.273
Marie?

47:40.357 --> 47:41.358
What are you doing?

47:41.692 --> 47:44.236
Careful. You're gonna scratch the do...

47:44.319 --> 47:45.821
Just wait a second, will you?

47:45.904 --> 47:47.239
I'll back the car out.

47:47.948 --> 47:49.324
Just let me help you.

47:49.867 --> 47:51.952
- Marie.
- Like you helped me with the police?

47:52.035 --> 47:53.161
What... what does that mean?

47:53.912 --> 47:55.247
What does that mean?

47:55.622 --> 47:58.417
I don't know what you were told
or what you heard,

47:58.500 --> 48:03.171
but I did not do...
I didn't do or say anything.

48:03.255 --> 48:04.089
- Let go.
- Listen.

48:04.172 --> 48:06.508
This sounds like a big miscommunication.

48:06.592 --> 48:09.720
I didn't tell the police anything
other than some background on you.

48:10.053 --> 48:12.681
I told them about where you'd been
and what you'd been through.

48:12.973 --> 48:14.308
That's it.

48:14.766 --> 48:17.394
I may have told them
you've been sensitive lately.

48:17.477 --> 48:19.146
But it's true, you have been.

48:19.438 --> 48:21.064
Now, don't do that.

48:21.148 --> 48:24.651
Don't pull a big disappearing act.
We are having a conversation here.

48:24.985 --> 48:26.236
Don't just abandon it.

48:26.570 --> 48:27.570
Marie!

48:27.863 --> 48:28.863
Marie.

48:46.423 --> 48:47.424
Marie.

48:48.800 --> 48:49.885
Could we talk a sec?

48:57.809 --> 48:58.977
I wasn't lying.

48:59.811 --> 49:01.063
What do you mean?

49:02.397 --> 49:04.274
I told the truth the first time.

49:04.358 --> 49:07.235
When you said you were raped?
You're saying that was true?

49:08.946 --> 49:12.157
- So why did you tell the police it wasn't?
- I don't know.

49:12.240 --> 49:15.160
I was really tired,
and they just kept pestering me.

49:15.243 --> 49:16.286
- Pestering?
- Yeah.

49:16.370 --> 49:18.789
Like, asking me the same question
over and over again.

49:18.872 --> 49:20.374
"How come your story doesn't add up?

49:20.457 --> 49:23.227
How come people don't believe you?
Is there really a rapist out there?"

49:23.251 --> 49:24.294
I just, I...

49:24.378 --> 49:26.463
I... I wanted to go home.

49:26.546 --> 49:29.758
If there is a rapist running around
and you've told the police there isn't,

49:29.841 --> 49:32.678
you need to go back
and clear that up, now.

49:32.761 --> 49:34.805
- But I gotta go to work.
- Marie.

49:35.263 --> 49:36.431
This is important.

49:40.102 --> 49:43.271
You wanna take back your statement,
taking back your statement.

49:45.816 --> 49:46.817
Yeah.

49:47.275 --> 49:49.403
All right, let's do this again.

49:55.158 --> 49:58.829
Detective Parker isn't in today.
This is Sergeant Rheinhart.

49:58.912 --> 50:00.414
How you doing, Marie?

50:01.373 --> 50:04.001
So, let's back up a little.

50:04.751 --> 50:06.586
Talk about what caused this turnaround.

50:06.878 --> 50:09.423
Did something happen last night
when you went home?

50:10.048 --> 50:12.426
Did... did they give you a hard time
about lying?

50:15.721 --> 50:16.721
- No.
- Really?

50:16.972 --> 50:20.559
'Cause those guys downstairs,
are they your counselors?

50:21.768 --> 50:23.311
- Yeah.
- Yeah, uh...

50:23.812 --> 50:25.897
they seemed kinda pissed off.

50:25.981 --> 50:27.399
And I get that.

50:27.482 --> 50:32.029
They put all this time and energy into
thinking this horrible thing happened.

50:32.112 --> 50:33.572
And then find out it didn't.

50:34.448 --> 50:35.449
I mean...

50:44.041 --> 50:46.043
I remember him on top of me.

50:49.755 --> 50:50.756
Marie...

50:53.050 --> 50:54.384
I know this is hard.

50:54.718 --> 50:56.094
And I'm sorry about that,

50:56.178 --> 50:59.181
but I have to remind you
of what's already happened.

51:00.015 --> 51:02.350
You already told us you lied.

51:02.434 --> 51:05.270
You already said you staged evidence.

51:05.604 --> 51:08.231
You swore to it. You signed your name.

51:08.315 --> 51:09.691
So, given that...

51:11.193 --> 51:12.861
how are we supposed to believe you now?

51:14.988 --> 51:18.241
I could...
I could take a lie detector test.

51:19.785 --> 51:21.661
Yeah, yeah... that's right.

51:22.788 --> 51:23.872
You could.

51:24.539 --> 51:25.832
That's an option.

51:26.458 --> 51:29.836
But you need to know,
if you take it and fail,

51:29.920 --> 51:32.464
that's called making a false statement.

51:33.090 --> 51:34.424
It's a crime.

51:35.342 --> 51:36.343
So...

51:37.594 --> 51:40.847
do you wanna go downstairs
for the polygraph?

51:40.931 --> 51:43.058
Or do you wanna just...

51:43.975 --> 51:47.104
clear this all up with us, in here?

51:47.395 --> 51:48.395
Um...

51:49.147 --> 51:50.148
maybe...

51:55.028 --> 51:56.446
maybe I was, um...

51:57.531 --> 51:58.573
hypnotized.

51:59.449 --> 52:02.786
You know what?
Fine, let's do the polygraph.

52:02.869 --> 52:05.622
Let's go. But here's the thing, Marie.

52:06.373 --> 52:07.624
The guy running it,

52:08.166 --> 52:10.043
he's not going to ask,

52:10.127 --> 52:13.839
"Were you hypnotized
into thinking you were raped?

52:14.506 --> 52:15.966
Did you dream a rape?"

52:16.383 --> 52:18.927
He's going to ask you one question.

52:19.427 --> 52:21.096
"Were you raped?"

52:21.179 --> 52:22.848
That's it.

52:23.306 --> 52:26.393
And if your answer turns out to be a lie,

52:26.476 --> 52:30.397
I have no choice but to arrest you
and put you in jail.

52:31.064 --> 52:32.399
Wait, why?

52:32.482 --> 52:34.882
Making a false statement
is a crime for a reason.

52:34.943 --> 52:38.113
It impedes our ability to do our job,
to keep the public safe.

52:38.196 --> 52:41.366
That's why we enforce it.
That's why we prosecute it.

52:42.826 --> 52:45.203
I also suspect
your living situation,

52:45.287 --> 52:47.956
with the counselors
and the stipends and all that...

52:48.039 --> 52:51.543
you lose all that
if you have a record, right?

52:52.627 --> 52:55.964
But, like I said,
if you want to do a polygraph,

52:56.047 --> 52:57.424
you're free to do one.

52:59.384 --> 53:01.136
You need to know the risks.

53:02.262 --> 53:03.388
But, yeah,

53:04.347 --> 53:06.057
the decision is yours.

53:20.280 --> 53:21.990
So, what's the story?

53:23.158 --> 53:24.158
Nope.

53:24.492 --> 53:25.577
Totally made up.

53:26.453 --> 53:29.664
Says she didn't think it would turn into
such a big thing.

53:30.457 --> 53:32.751
- So, we're gonna close the case.
- Right.

53:34.502 --> 53:36.421
Call me if you have any questions.

53:36.504 --> 53:37.672
Yeah, thank you.

53:47.807 --> 53:48.993
Why would you do that?

53:49.017 --> 53:50.936
Why would you freak us out like that?
That's...

53:51.019 --> 53:52.339
It's sick is what it is.

53:52.562 --> 53:55.041
- You're sick, you are.
- You knew how scared this would make us.

53:55.065 --> 53:57.609
Guys, let's try to put this in terms
of feelings.

53:57.692 --> 53:58.610
I'm feeling mad.

53:58.693 --> 53:59.945
- Betrayed.
- Disgusted.

54:00.028 --> 54:01.947
Angry, really, really angry.

54:04.366 --> 54:07.035
Marie, do you want to say anything?

54:35.021 --> 54:36.064
That's insane.

54:41.403 --> 54:42.404
- Amelia.
- No.

54:42.487 --> 54:43.822
Okay? Just, no.

